Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Knidian pottery transport amphora to moderate turn. Clay medium red-brown. Circular stamp with hexafoil symbol.
Type series: KT691 (Virginia Grace's unpublished K(nidian) T(ype) series)
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 31, 49. Names, Zenodotos, Hephaistion
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0306)
